result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Donald P. Gilligan was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Credit for 2 days only if revoked.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.
The defendant may not consume or possess alcohol and no entry into any bar, tavern or establishments that sell liquor.
The defendant must submit a DNA sample with surcharge assessed.

The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

The defendant must attend at least one NA/AA or similar meeting per week.

The defendant must follow thru with any and all previous recommendations and/or treatment plan from recent inpatient treatment.

timeConds.notes: Huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3).

records.addlTxt: Defendant Donald P. Gilligan in court with attorney Dennis Michael Melowski.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:03 AM. Also called 14TR704 and 14TR705. State - resolved - plead g/nc to count #1 as alleged, dismiss count #2 and all companion citations, joint recommendation of a withheld sentence, place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: 10 months in FC jail with huber - credit for 2 days, 24 month DL revocation consecutive to jail sentence, $600.00 fine plus costs - apply bond posted, IID. Melowski agrees as does Gilligan. Gilligan pleads NC to count #1 as alleged. Court dismisses counts #2 and 14TR704 and 14TR705. Court handed plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts, plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. Defendant acknowledges 5 prior OWI convictions. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Melowski makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Gilligan makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #1 - impose 5 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 2 years of extended supervision, stayed, place on probation for 3 years with conditions of: fine of $5000.00 inclusive of costs - take bond posted, 1 year in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - 2 days credit only if revoked - report today, AODA and follow thru, follow thru with any recommendations or treatment conditions as a result of recent inpatient treatment, attend AA/NA or similar treatment program once a week, 24 month DL revocation, IID on DL and all vehicles titled in his name for 3 years commencing upun issuance of valid DL, no consumption or possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns or establishments that sells alcohol, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, submit DNA sample with surcharge assessed - paid thru probation, eligible for programs if revoked, no voting rights, no possession of firearms, right to appeal, find 14TR704 reasonable adjourned.

Defendant Donald P. Gilligan in court, with attorney Dennis Michael Melowski appearing telephonically.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 11:06 a.m. Also called 14TR704 & 14TR705. Court - has received correspondence that agreement has been made. Melowski - there is an agreement but asking for time before starting his sentence for stated reasons and asks for a PLEAS date in August. Discussion in regards to new employment/training and huber. State - does not object to setting out PLEAS until August, but maybe just set out 30 days. Court - feels incarceration would not interfere with probationary period for new job. Melowski makes comment. Court responds. Court will consider plea rejected and set for JT, advises if plea offer still exists at this time and does not believe this is an adjournment for job related issues. Melowski questions court. Court explains procedure. Melowski asks court to just set a PLEAS as there is an agreement. Court schedules PLEAS. Bond continued.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 5, 2015 at 11:00 pm.

Defendant Donald P. Gilligan in court with attorney Dennis Michael Melowski - who appears telephonically.  Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:25 PM. Also called 14TR704 and 14TR705 which is set for a refusal hearing (14TR705). Melowski believes we are only here for status conference on criminal matter for stated reasons (treatment for defendant). Defendant informs court that he completed treatment and was discharged on 4/30/15. Bednar asking for an adjournment and will state that the refusal was reasonable upon a plea on criminal matter. Melowski would like to re-visit negotiations with the State for stated reasons. Court responds. Melowski responds. Court continues bond and sets for FPT - Melowski needs to be in person if it will be a plea, otherwise it will be set for JT, traffic matters to track and set as STC.  Final pre-trial scheduled for June 1, 2015 at 11:00 am.

Defendant Donald P. Gilligan in court.  Attorney Dennis Melowski appears telephonically. Jodie L. Bednar appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:19 PM. Also called 14TR704 and 14TR705. Melowski - waiver of PH today, asking for adjourned ARGN date for stated reasons (defendant enrolling in inpatient treatment). State - no objections to an adjourned ARGN. Gilligan understands that he will be waiving the PH today. Court does verbal connalquey of waiver of PH, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial, continues bond, discussion on adjourned date for ARGN. Traffic matters will track with criminal matter. State - proceed with ARGN today and then set for STC instead of FPT. Melowski agrees. State files Information that mirrors complaint. Melowski will waive reading of the Information and proceeds to ARGN and enters NG pleas to all counts. Court continues bond, set for FPT.  Status conference scheduled for May 6, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
